Remo cum fratre Quirinus .- according to the common legend Remus was slain by his brother Romulus in a quarrel. So we may translate, ‘Romulus reconciled with his brother Remus', referring to the restoration oi concord after the civil wars. Quirinus was a Sabine god oi war: Romulus aiter his apotheosis was identified with him.

Belli portaez the representation of the gates of War im- prisoning Fury is merely a fancy oi the poet's, with an allusion of course to the closing of the doors of the Temple of J anus in periods of peace.
